                             | Default value                                         |\n74:| `kubernetes.disable.autoConfig` / `KUBERNETES_DISABLE_AUTOCONFIG`                                               | Disable automatic configuration (KubernetesClient would not look in `~/.kube/config`, mounted ServiceAccount, environment variables or System properties for Kubernetes cluster information)                                                                                                         | `false`                                               |\n83:| `kubernetes.certs.client.file` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_FILE`                                                 |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n84:| `kubernetes.certs.client.data` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_DATA`                                                 |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n85:| `kubernetes.certs.client.key.file` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_KEY_FILE`                                         |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n86:| `kubernetes.certs.client.key.data` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_KEY_DATA`                                         |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n87:| `kubernetes.certs.client.key.algo` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_KEY_ALGO`                                         | Client key encryption algorithm                                                                                                          | `RSA`                                                 |\n88:| `kubernetes.certs.client.key.passphrase` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_KEY_PASSPHRASE`                             |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n92:| `kubernetes.auth.tryKubeConfig` / `KUBERNETES_AUTH_TRYKUBECONFIG`                                               | Configure client using Kubernetes config                                                                                                 | `true`                                                |\n93:| `kubeconfig` / `KUBECONFIG`                                                                                     | Name of the kubernetes config file to read                                                                                               | `~/.kube/config`                                      |\n94:| `kubernetes.auth.tryServiceAccount` / `KUBERNETES_AUTH_TRYSERVICEACCOUNT`                                       | Configure client from Service account                                                                                                    | `true`                                                |\n95:| `kubernetes.tryNamespacePath` / `KUBERNETES_TRYNAMESPACEPATH`                                                   | Configure client namespace from Kubernetes service account namespace path                                                                | `true`                                                |\n121:| `http.proxy` / `HTTP_PROXY`                                                                                     | URL to the [proxy](http://www.gnu.org/software/wget/manual/html_node/Proxies.html) for HTTP requests (See [Proxy precedence](./doc/FAQ.md#how-does-kubernetesclient-loads-proxy-url-from-various-sources))                                    |                                                       |\n122:| `https.proxy` / `HTTPS_PROXY`                                                                                   | URL to the [proxy](http://www.gnu.org/software/wget/manual/html_node/Proxies.html) for HTTPS requests (See [Proxy precedence](./doc/FAQ.md#how-does-kubernetesclient-loads-proxy-url-from-various-sources))                                   |                                                       |\n124:Alternatively you can use the `ConfigBuilder` to create a config object for the Kubernetes client:\n127:Config config = new ConfigBuilder().withMasterUrl(\"https://mymaster.com\").build();\n128:KubernetesClient client = new KubernetesClientBuilder().withConfig(config).build();\n137:NamespaceList myNs = client.namespaces().list();\n139:ServiceList myServices = client.services().list();\n141:ServiceList myNsServices = client.services().inNamespace(\"default\").list();\n147:Namespace myns = client.namespaces().withName(\"myns\").get();\n149:Service myservice = client.services().inNamespace(\"default\").withName(\"myservice\").get();\n155:Namespace myns = client.namespaces().withName(\"myns\").delete();\n157:Service myservice = client.services().inNamespace(\"default\").withName(\"myservice\").delete();\n163:Namespace myns = client.namespaces().withName(\"myns\").edit(n -> new NamespaceBuilder(n)\n169:Service myservice = client.services().inNamespace(\"default\").withName(\"myservice\").edit(s -> new ServiceBuilder(s)\n179:Namespace myns = client.namespaces().create(new NamespaceBuilder()\n186:Service myservice = client.services().inNamespace(\"default\").create(new ServiceBuilder()\n212:client.events().inAnyNamespace().watch(new Watcher<>() {\n234:jobs = client.batch().jobs().list();\n239:There are cases where you want to read a resource from an external source, rather than defining it using the clients DSL.\n240:For those cases the client allows you to load the resource from:\n250:    Pod refreshed = client.load('/path/to/a/pod.yml').fromServer().get();\n251:    client.load('/workspace/pod.yml').delete();\n252:    LogWatch handle = client.load('/workspace/pod.yml').watchLog(System.out);\n254:### Passing a reference of a resource to the client\n261:    client.resource(pod).delete();\n263:### Adapting the client\n265:The client supports plug-able adapters. An example adapter is the [OpenShift Adapter](openshift-client/src/main/java/io/fabric8/openshift/client/impl/OpenShiftExtensionAdapter.java)\n266:which allows adapting an existing [KubernetesClient](kubernetes-client-api/src/main/java/io/fabric8/kubernetes/client/KubernetesClient.java) instance to an [OpenShiftClient](openshift-client-api/src/main/java/io/fabric8/openshift/client/OpenShiftClient.java) one.\n271:KubernetesClient client = new KubernetesClientBuilder().build();\n273:OpenShiftClient oClient = client.adapt(OpenShiftClient.class);\n276:The client also support the isAdaptable() method which checks if the adaptation is possible and returns true if it does.\n279:KubernetesClient client = new KubernetesClientBuilder().build();\n280:if (client.isAdaptable(OpenShiftClient.class)) {\n281:    OpenShiftClient oClient = client.adapt(OpenShiftClient.class);\n283:    throw new Exception(\"Adapting to OpenShiftClient not support. Check if adapter is present, and that env provides /oapi root path.\");\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1783793999977}}
